---
alwaysApply: true
---


Cursor Rule — Icons

Never import icons directly from lucide-react in components

All lucide-react icons must be added to src/components/icons.tsx

Use only the centralized icons object:

import { icons } from "@/components/icons";

Reference icons via icons.iconName (camelCase)

Icons are exported as JSX elements, not inline components

Exceptions: shadcn/ui internal imports are allowed.


Cursor Rule — Toast Notifications

Always use Sonner (shadcn/ui) for toast notifications

Never use showAlert from @src/module/ods or any other toast/alert system

Import toast from sonner:

import { toast } from "sonner";

Use toast methods:
- toast.success("Message") for success notifications
- toast.error("Message") for error notifications
- toast.info("Message") for info notifications
- toast.warning("Message") for warning notifications

The Toaster component is already set up in src/index.jsx, so no additional setup is needed

When migrating existing code, replace all showAlert calls with appropriate toast methods


Always use JSX syntax for React components and UI rendering

Never use React.createElement directly

All React UI must be written using JSX:
- <div>, <Component />, <>...</>

Assume JSX is enabled via modern React (react-jsx transform)

Do not generate or refactor code into React.createElement under any circumstances

Prefer functional components with JSX returns

Cursor Rule — Styling (Tailwind CSS Only)

Always use Tailwind CSS for styling

Never write, import, or reference custom CSS files
- No `.css`, `.scss`, `.sass`, or `.less`
- No CSS Modules

Do not use:
- Inline styles (`style={{ ... }}`)
- Styled-components
- Any CSS-in-JS solution

All styling must be done using Tailwind utility classes in **JS, JSX, TS, or TSX**:
- `className="flex items-center gap-2"`
- `className="text-sm font-medium text-muted-foreground"`
